I was not sure what to expect but it was gritty, realistic and covered multiple facets of human decision making.

On a positive note, the movie makes a statement about the state of dysfunction of relationships in the black community often caused by our men being unable to provide for their families, due to a large number of them who have been in the prison system. Several story lines portraying ways that black women, though they love their men, often are tired and beat them down and how those with good men will sometimes tear them down and cheat on them.
Also depicted is how murder for nonsensical reasons is a common occurrence. Some characters were a bit too over the top and the movie made no attempt to make the plot realistic. For example, a bank manager would not have been allowed to make a decision on her cousin's loan. A psychologist or psychiatrist would not have been treating his sister in law, nor would it be wise for him to counsel women about their sex lives one on one. There were several humorous moments,so not a bad way to spend 90 minutes of your life.

I will give it a E for effort. I don't knock anyone who makes a film and gets it to the public. The script was confusing in the beginning. I thought Malcolm was a church minister and was doing counseling sessions. After the movie keep going I realized that he was just a counselor. The story line was not too bad to be honest the movie just needed help technically. Whoever was the DP needs some more skills the camera work was not solid. The shots were shaky and the use of lens with the focus was off. If this is there first time shooting then I understand but at the end of the day the entire movies falls back on the EP and the Director. The film had it's moments I would like to see more work from Elyse. I support film makers that have the gumption to make a film. Congrats getting your movie to Amazon Prime this is no small feet. The actors are close friend and family members I can tell but hey when you budget is tight you use who can work with and for you. The young man that played the drug dealer was highly believable. The bank manager was a little over the top. The boyfriend that was stressed about selling drugs to support his family was a good character actor as well. Keep making movies that's the only way to get better and let people other than your close friends critic the films that you are making and they will point out what's believable and what looks good technically and what does not. Hope this helps.

This got to be about the dumbest movie EVER. 1.) Too many storylines... just Underwhelming. with poor conclusion 2.) the acting was okay at best could be better, but honestly not expecting the acting to be mind-blowing 3.) The storylines left me feeling like I really wasted 1.5 hours of my time watching this... 4.) the way the characters interacted and Finally came together at the end was not worth it. 5.) it should have been called something else, the title "Behind closed Doors" Why? This did not elude to behind close doors. More like "Practice what you preach" OR another type of title eluding to giving and taking advice, talking to a mediator.. bad title 6.) Did I mention the storyline is terrible? Just bad..... 7.) Even the Main Characters story didn't fit NONE of the stories flowed effortlessly into each other and why are characters' from other storylines overlapping?  8.) THE ENDING...? Now Unless you just want background noise watch it, if not, keep scrolling.

This low budget "script" of someone getting some people together and said "let's call ourselves acting by reading these lines with the worst stereotypical dialogue and make it a movie!" Between the woman complaining to the 'pastor' about her husband asking for oral pleasure, I couldn't get past all the head wagging...the bank manager couldn't speak any better to the employees???

Had they actually rehearsed or studied the lines to follow, it could've been better!!!! The profanity in the church in counseling, the "ghettoness" of it all...I stopped torturing myself after the bank manager scene!!! What was all the attitude and rachetness about? I didn't understand what was the point of the chick in the driveway doing stretches...IN THE COLD...in regular clothes!!!! Whack and a waste of time!!!!

It's "okay" because the acting is so horrible. But here's what is good about this movie....it's real life situations and it hits home with many people.  Just like in the movie everyone had an epiphany about their own life, so maybe this will help someone who needs it as well. Even with the bad acting you can see clearly what they are trying to show you. The funniest actress was the church going woman. She had me cracking up with all her scenes.  Check it out only if you have time to do nothing and you are trying to escape from being bored.
